With due consideration for conditions existing in nature and for the importance of outdoor adventure experiences, the regulations shall include:
Safety procedures for:
Aquatic programs;
Horseback riding;
Firearms control;
Riflery;
Archery;
Adventure camps;
Artistic gymnastics;
Hang gliding;
Road cycling;
Skiing;
Rock climbing;
Spelunking;
Motorized vehicle activities;
Rappelling; or
High ropes;
Except for outdoor cookouts, sanitation regulations pertaining to the facilities and personnel for the storage, preparation, and serving of food products;
Personal health, first aid, and medical services, health supervision, and the maintenance of health records for campers;
Water supplies, sewage disposal systems, and refuse collection and disposal procedures;
Fire and safety standards relating to the buildings and the occupants of buildings;
Systems for the routine reporting of fatalities and serious illnesses or accidents;
Any personnel screening procedures that are required for operators and employees of group day care centers;
Procedures for conducting inspection, monitoring compliance, and verifying information;
Alternate accreditation which has been approved by the Secretary; and
Minimum standards for the supervision of campers during routine activities.
